<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Online Survey</title>

    <!-- Bootstrap -->
    <link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- HTML5 shim and Respond.js for IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
    <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->
    <!--[if lt IE 9]>
      <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js"></script>
      <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
    <![endif]-->
  </head>
  <body>
      <body>

    <div class="container">

      <!-- Static navbar -->
      <nav class="navbar navbar-inverse">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <div class="navbar-header">
            <button type="button" class="navbar-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#navbar" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="navbar">
              <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            </button>
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">Survey</a>
          </div>
          <div id="navbar" class="navbar-collapse collapse">
            <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
              <li class="active"><a href="/">Home</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div><!--/.nav-collapse -->
        </div><!--/.container-fluid -->
      </nav>
      {% if isShowAlert == true %}
        <div class="alert alert-danger alert-dismissible" role="alert">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
        <strong>Oops!</strong> It seems that you have done this survery before.
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      

      <!-- Main component for a primary marketing message or call to action -->
      <div class="jumbotron">
      <div style="text-align:center;"><h1>Survey for social media impact</h1></div>
        
        
        <p>Thank you for participating in this study. This is an academic study aimed at understanding your Facebook usage. There are <b>two steps</b> to complete the study. </p>
        <p><b>Step 1:</b> You need to give permission to access your Facebook profile, friend list, posts, photos, videos, messages and your friends’ comments on your posts. 
        </p>
        <p><b>Step 2:</b> You will be given a survey ID after you finish step 1. Copy the survey ID, and click the link to an online survey. Paste the survey ID as the answer to the first question of the online survey. Complete the rest part of the online survey.
        </p>
        
        <br>
        <p>After you finish these two steps, you will be given $10 as reimbursement for your effort. Please be informed that all information recorded in this study will be kept strictly confidential, and will only be used for research purposes.</p>
        <p>If you have any queries, please contact Mr.Haifeng Xu at <a href="mailto:xu-haif@comp.nus.edu.sg">xu-haif@comp.nus.edu.sg</a>. Thank you.</p>
        <p>Now please click the following button to give us permission to access your Facebook profile, friend list, posts, photos, videos, messages and your friends’ comments on your posts. 
        <br>
        </p>
        <p style="margin:0 auto; text-align:center;">

          <a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal" role="button">Start</a>

        </p>
      </div>

    </div> <!-- /container -->

    <div class="modal fade" id="myModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="modal-dialog">
        <div class="modal-content">
          <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
            <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Attention:</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-body">
            Facebook Usage app will receive the following info: your public profile, friend list, posts, messages, comments, photos and videos.
            <br>
            <b>* Please do not close your browser until a finishing page shows up. Thank you.</b>
            <br>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-footer">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-danger" data-dismiss="modal">Cancel</button>
            <a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" href={{loginURL}}>Login Now</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
    <script src="js/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->
    <script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>



